Changing Nouns or Verbs into Adjectives

Noun or Verb

center, music, nation + al
beauty, care, help, pain, use, success + ful
care, pain, use + less
comfort, fashion + able
dirt, health, rain, wind + y
danger, fame + ous
act, attract, expense + ive

Adjective

central, musical, national
beautiful, careful, helpful, painful, useful, successful
careless, painless, useless
comfortable, fashionable
dirty, healthy, rainy, windy
dangerous, famous
active, attractive, expensive

The spelling often changes when we add letters to a word that ends with a vowel or y
fame -> famous
expense -> expensive
beauty -> beautiful
